@node Overview
@chapter Overview

@samp{claude-code-extras.el} extends @samp{claude-code}, the Emacs package that runs Claude Code sessions inside an Eat terminal buffer. While @samp{claude-code} provides the core session management and terminal integration, this extras package layers on several quality-of-life features that make extended Claude sessions more manageable.

The package provides five main areas of functionality:

@itemize
@item
@strong{Session switching.} A Consult-powered interface for starting new Claude sessions or switching between existing ones, with live buffer previews (@ref{Session switching}).
@item
@strong{Conversation logging.} Automatic periodic saving of terminal buffer contents to timestamped log files, with detection of conversation clears (@ref{Logging}).
@item
@strong{Status polling.} Integration with a statusline script that exports session metadata (model name, cost, context usage, token counts) as JSON, polled periodically and exposed through accessor functions (@ref{Status polling}).
@item
@strong{Alerts.} Configurable OS notifications (visual, audible, or both) when Claude finishes responding, triggered by a hook-based stop event (@ref{Alerts}).
@item
@strong{Buffer lifecycle.} Kill protection for active sessions, automatic buffer cleanup on process exit, and a SIGWINCH workaround for terminal rendering glitches (@ref{Buffer lifecycle}).
@end itemize

The package depends on @samp{claude-code}, @samp{consult} (for the session switcher), and @samp{paths} (for the log directory default).

