@node Session switching
@section Session switching

@findex claude-code-extras-start-or-switch
The command @code{claude-code-extras-start-or-switch} is the main entry point for working with Claude sessions. When no Claude sessions are active, it starts a new one by calling @code{claude-code}. When one or more sessions exist, it opens a Consult selection interface listing all active sessions plus a ``[new session]'' option.

Sessions are displayed by project name (extracted from the buffer name). When multiple sessions share the same project, the instance name is appended for disambiguation (e.g. ``project:instance''). The interface provides live buffer previews as you navigate the candidates, so you can see the current state of each session before switching.

@node Toggling alerts
@section Toggling alerts

@findex claude-code-extras-toggle-alert
The command @code{claude-code-extras-toggle-alert} toggles the buffer-local value of @code{claude-code-extras-alert-on-ready} and reports the new state. This is useful during long-running operations: enable alerts before submitting a complex prompt, then disable them when you return to interactive use. The alert style and sound are configured via the user options described in @ref{Alert options}.

